This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and specifically addresses the issue of modeling word order in neural networks. Additionally, the paper also presents experiments on text classification, machine translation, and language modeling, which are all tasks within the scope of cs.CL. 

The paper also involves the use of neural networks, which is a common theme in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

Furthermore, the paper introduces a novel solution for modeling word order using complex embeddings, which involves the use of mathematical concepts such as continuous functions and imaginary numbers. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision), which often involve the use of advanced mathematical techniques in their research.
